s a part of religious ceremonies is still strong, the traditional paper and bamboo objects are being more and more often replaced by plastic components and whole preprinted cardboard counterparts. The resulting changes in the personal, business, and especially the creative and artistic side of the craft are therefore also addressed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aCRAFTS & HOBBIES / Papercrafts.2bisacsh1 aLiu, Helen Hui-ling, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361783440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503617834423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503617834/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles